titleStmt.title: Taxonomy for Concepts defined in the Thesaurus Linguae Sericae

sourceDesc.p: Compiled from the implicit structure of linked concepts. Unfortunately, it seems that their are circular or inverse mappings, maybe due to a confusion between hypernym and hyponym

revisionDesc.change:
Compiled the taxonomy, split into the following trees:
A major tree, emanating from the concept PRIME
A 'garbage' tree, starting with N/A, collecting all items that are explicitly linking here
A separate tree of items that where empirically not linked in the above two trees, thus a collection of islands, starting at Not def.
Due to these problems, some concepts appear more than one time in the taxonomy. In these cases, the one appearing first in the file has been chosen as the temporary stand-in, with the other versions instead getting a @corresp attribute that points to the first instance. It might be useful at some point to go over them and choose the right ones.
